            <title xml:id="name970-2" xml:lang="fr-x-bhsyre" source="#bib970-1">Šarbēl</title>
            <title xml:id="name970-3" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib970-1">De Sharbel</title>
            <title xml:id="name970-4"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   source="#bib970-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">On Sharbel</title>
            <author xml:lang="fr" source="#bib970-1">Jacques de Serugh</author>
            <note xml:lang="syr" type="incipit" source="#bib970-1">
               <quote>ܫܪܒܝܠ ܟܘܡܪܐ ܕܗܘܐ ܣܗܕܐ ܒܚܪܬ ܝܘ̈ܡܘܗܝ ܬܒܥܢܝ ܡܐܡܪܐ ܗܒ ܠܝ ܡܪܢ ܕܥܠܘܗܝ ܐܡܪ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="incipit" source="#bib970-1">
               <quote>Le prêtre des idoles Sharbêl qui devint martyr à la fin de ses jours m’a demandé un discours; donne-moi, Seigneur, de parler de lui.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="syr" type="explicit" source="#bib970-1">
               <quote>ܒܕܡܐ ܡܟܝܪܐ ܘܕܡܐ ܫܩܠܬ ܘܕܡܐ ܝܗܒܬ ܒܪܝܟ ܕܒܚܘܒܗ ܠܕܡܐ ܕܣܗ̈ܕܐ ܚܠܛ ܥܡ ܕܝܠܗ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="explicit" source="#bib970-1">
               <quote>Fiancée par le sang elle a reçu et donné le sang; béni soit celui qui dans son amour mêle le sang des maryrs au sien.</quote>
            </note>
            <note type="editions">
               <bibl source="#bib970-1">
                  <author>Mösinger, G.</author>
                  <title>Monumenta Syriaca ex Romanis codicibus collecta II</title>
                  <citedRange>Oeniponti, 1878, p. 52-63</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib970-1">
               <bibl n="1">(Edited Above): ms Vatican, Borgia Syr. 128, f. 170v-175v</bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib970-1">
               <bibl>ms Oxford, Bodleian Library, syr. 135 (Poc. 404), f. 324-327</bibl>
            </note>
